body:
@ValentinOdier  raised this issue on dwopen with a phantomjs action that ran into 

```
QEventDispatcherUNIXPrivate(): Unable to create thread pipe: Too many open files
```

I asked him to link his code here for us to test and discuss.

@perryibm good point this is a delicate issue and we need to be diligent.

@gconan could you try adding a different tag to your Cartfile.  I see you are building for Swift 2.2.  Versions of the mobile SDK 0.2.0 and above are Swift 3.

github "openwhisk/openwhisk-client-swift.git" === 0.1.7

It also occurs to me that the latest version of the starter app is also Swift 3.  Did you need a Swift 2.2 version?

@rabbah @sjfink 
for less disruption: can we do a `docker version` at invoker startup to collect the server version and branch off into the config.json reader if version >= 1.12.x and just keep the old code otherwise? this would be like a feature-toggle and @perryibm would not have to wait until all systems are on 1.12.

we will probably need to check for kernel version, too. some security features only work on certain kernel levels.
